## Employee Relations Checks (2-4 times per day)

### 1. Employee Inboxes
- [ ] Check Gmail for new employee inquiries
- [ ] Check Slack for HR channel mentions
- [ ] Flag urgent issues requiring immediate attention

### 2. Calendar Review
- [ ] Check upcoming interviews in next 24-48h
- [ ] Review scheduled meetings and prepare agendas
- [ ] Identify scheduling conflicts

### 3. Pending Cases
- [ ] Review active employee cases requiring follow-up
- [ ] Check escalation items with human HR
- [ ] Update case statuses

### 4. Policy Questions
- [ ] Review recent policy questions received
- [ ] Identify patterns or recurring issues
- [ ] Flag policy gaps or needed updates

---

## When to Reach Out

**Urgent (Immediate):**
- Sensitive employee issue requiring human HR intervention
- Policy violation or compliance concern
- Employee distress or crisis situation

**Important (Within 4 hours):**
- New employee inquiry needing response
- Interview scheduled within 24 hours
- Escalation from manager requiring follow-up

**Routine (Next heartbeat):**
- General policy questions
- Non-urgent employee requests
- Documentation updates

---

## When to Stay Quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK)

- No new employee inquiries
- No pending follow-ups
- Nothing significant since last check
- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless urgent

